<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb9961aa3-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s3235"><num value="3235">§ 3235.</num><heading> Venue in capital cases</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The trial of offenses punishable with death shall be had in the county where the offense was committed, where that can be done without great inconvenience.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb9961aa4-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645">June 25, 1948, ch. 645</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/826">62 Stat. 826</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
